   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CARE Opportunities for Mother &amp; Infant Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Opportunities for Mother and Infant Development (OMID) initiative addresses barriers to safe deliveries through a community-based approach in Afghanistan, where one out of every nine women dies from pregnancy- and childbirth-related complications, one of the most severe maternal mortality ratios in the world. By promoting community support groups, CARE encourages pregnant women and their families to plan for births and to take prompt action when emergencies arise.</narrative>
  </description>
